Class Task

java.lang.Object
  fr.unilim.javance.projet.internal.Task
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Cloneable
public class Task
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Cloneable

A task in a "todo" This class defines a task in the todo application implementation. There is a set of properties. A task has:

  • a unique identifier id. It two tasks have the same id, they refer to the same task,
  • a title which is also the task label (a short description),
  • a more complete description,
  • the creation date,
  • a due date,
  • a status defined by the enum fr.unilim.javance.project.internal.TaskStatus,
  • an address,
  • and a folder.

Author:
Amaury Gauthier, David Pequegnot
